Around off, on a length, shaping in, Jermaine defends it to covers.
Again there is plenty of inward movement behind this good-length delivery, Jermaine Blackwood flicks it to mid-wicket.

Shortish and around off, Blackwood gets across and works it towards short leg. The fielder there doesn't get down in time but does well to stick his right foot out and deflects it towards square leg. Prevents at least a run with his smartness.
In the channel outside off, Jermaine Blackwood shoulders arms to end the over.
Fuller in length and around off, Mayers drives it wide of the cover fielder and picks up a single.
Slightly short and on middle, Blackwood flicks it off his pads but finds the short leg fielder.
Very full this time, around off, Jermaine drives it back towards the bowler. He fails to stop cleanly and it goes on to hit the stumps at the non-striker's end.
Leans forward to a full ball and defends it down.
Floated and full around off, Jermaine presses forward and defends it on the leg side.
Flatter and quicker on middle, a bit on the shorter side, Jermaine Blackwood moves inside the crease and blocks it down.
Swing and a miss! Short in length and outside off, keeping low, Kyle Mayers is early into his cross-batted shot and misses. He needs to be careful with his shot selection on this tricky surface.
Another play and a miss! It seems that Kyle Mayers will bat his way. Short in length and wide outside off, Mayers tries to cut away from his body and misses.
Uppish! Back of a length, outside off, and holding off the surface, Mayers stands back and plays a mistimed pull shot. It flies over the bowler and the mid on fielder cuts it off.
Shortish and on off, Mayers swivels on the back foot with his pull shot but only manages to drag it off the bottom edge to mid on. Kyle is living dangerously at the moment.

Four leg byes! Valuable runs for the home team. Sliding down the leg side, on a length from 'round the wicket, Mayers tries to flick but misses. It brushes his pads and scoots away to the fine leg fence.

FOUR! Risky shot! Kyle Mayers continues to take risks. Short in length and outside off, Mayers reaches out for it as he throws the bat through the line. It takes the outside edge and flies down to third man for a boundary.
Full and floated on off, defended back.
Shorter on off, Blackwood goes back and turns it to mid-wicket.
Slower through the air, short and on off, Jermaine defends it down from the back foot.
FOUR! Risky attempt from Blackwood there as he was a long way across the stumps. Spinning down the leg side, Jermaine gets a faint tickle behind the ball as it races down to fine leg. 150 comes up!
Fuller and around off, Blackwood knocks it down to mid on and races across to the other end.
Floated and full, around middle and skidding in, Mayers leans forward to defend but gets an inside edge. It goes to short leg.

Four leg byes! West Indies continue to get some bonus runs here. Back of a length, around middle and leg with extra bounce, Blackwood tries to glance but misses. It kisses his thigh pad and screams away to the fine leg fence.
Fraction short and on off, Jermaine Blackwood defends it solidly from the back foot.
Fuller in length, around off, Blackwood pushes it firmly to mid off.
Shortish and wide outside off, Jermaine Blackwood defends it from the back foot to the off side.
Again the length is on the shorter side, around off, Blackwood defends it with his elbow pointing skyward.
Around off on a length, the batter has just watchfully blocked this out.
Loopy delivery, landing full and outside off, Mayers drives it with gentle hands through covers and picks up a single.
Tossed up, full and on off, Jermaine defends it back towards the bowler.
Slower through the air, full and on off, turning in, Blackwood fails to flick and it goes off his pads, past short leg. They cross for a leg bye.
Fires it in, flat and short around off, Kyle Mayers defends it from the back foot.
Keeps it full and around leg, Mayers drills it down the ground but finds mid on.
Drifting down the leg side, Kyle eases it off his pads but finds the fielder at backward square leg.
Angling across the batter, on a good length outside off, Jermaine Blackwood allows it through.
On a length again, around middle and leg, Blackwood defends it down from the back foot.
Wayward delivery, on a good length and down the leg side, Blackwood tries to buy some cheap runs but fails to connect with his attempted flick shot.
In the zone around off, on a length and angling away, Blackwood covers his stumps and shoulders arms.
Fuller in length and outside off, Blackwood plants his front foot forward and then makes a leave.
Fullish and around off, Jermaine Blackwood forces it back towards the bowler who fails to collect it and deflects it to mid on. Maiden.
Full and around off, Mayers strides forward and defends it to the off side.

SIX! Boom! Some extra flight on this delivery, full and landing around off, Mayers finds it in his hitting area and lifts it cleanly over long off for a biggie. Right in the arc and it's a risk-free shot.
Flatter and on off, short in length, Mayers punches but finds the fielder at cover-point.
Quicker delivery, around middle and leg, helped to mid-wicket.
Flighted and full, outside off, Mayers drives it through mid off and collects a single. Hit a maximum to force the field back and then collect a single, smart!
Loopy and full, around off, Jermaine Blackwood defends it by striding forward. 7 from the over, West Indies trail by 70 runs.
A full delivery on middle. Mayers pushes it to mid on.

FOUR! In that gap again, the second slip is wide than usual and the ball runs away through that gap for a boundary. Lands on a good length, outside off. Mayers drives it with hard hands and gets a thick outside edge. The ball runs through the gap between first slip and wide second slip for a boundary.
Back of a length, on off, Mayers punches it through cover-point for a couple of runs.
Good yorker this time on middle. However, Mayers also does well to get his bat down in time.
Islam follows a yorker with a bouncer. On middle and Mayers ducks under it.
FOUR! Another short ball and this time Mayers hammers it away! Short and around off. Mayers is into the position early and pulls it towards the mid-wicket fence for a boundary.
Slower through the air, on middle. Jermaine Blackwood defends it back to the bowler.
On middle and pitched up this time. Jermaine Blackwood works it to mid-wicket.
Flatter delivery on off. Jermaine Blackwood is solid in his defense.
Pitches on middle from 'round the wicket. It turns into Jermaine Blackwood a bit as he goes back and blocks it.
Goes flatter and quicker on middle. Jermaine Blackwood defends it nicely again.
FOUR! Nicely played! This is fuller on the pads. Jermaine Blackwood kneels and sweeps it through the backward square leg region for a boundary.
Lands on a length, on off. Mayers blocks it solidly from his crease.
Serves a length delivery again, around off. Mayers gets a good stride forward and pushes it towards covers.
Same length, around off. Maybe a tad short and Mayers pushes it towards point as he opens the face of his blade.

Excellent delivery! Gets some good bounce this time. Lands on a length, around off. It bounces sharply and beats Mayers who tries to push it away. The bowler appeals but he himself is not convinced. The finger stays down and Shakib looks away.
A length delivery on off. Mayers defends it with the middle of his blade.
Goes a tad fuller on off. Mayers drives but finds the fielder at short cover.

FOUR! Fifty partnership comes up with that boundary! Hasan drifts on the pads. Jermaine Blackwood sweeps and sweeps it fine. The ball races away towards the fine leg fence. West Indies trail by 52 runs.
Goes quicker and flatter on off. Jermaine Blackwood defends it from his crease.
Pushes it quicker again on off. Jermaine Blackwood with a solid block again.
Goes slightly shorter on off. Jermaine Blackwood uses the depth of the crease and defends it.
Short and wide outside off. Jermaine Blackwood cuts it to the point fielder.
Hasan bowls closer to the off pole and Jermaine Blackwood is ready with his defensive block.
FOUR! Cracking shot! This is overpitched outside off. Mayers lunges forward and drives it beautifully through covers for a boundary. The deficit drops below 50 now.
Islam responds with a bouncer on off. Mayers sways away from the line of the ball.
Back of a length, around off. Mayers guides it through backward point for a single.
Lands on a length, on off. Jermaine Blackwood blocks it off the front foot.

Bit of misunderstanding between the batters but no damage is done in the end! Fullish delivery on off. Jermaine Blackwood drives it to mid off. Mayers, at the non-striker's end, wants a single but is sent back in time by Blackwood.
A fullish delivery, outside off. Jermaine Blackwood leaves it alone.
A flatter and shorter delivery on off. Mayers blocks it out.
On the shorter side again, on off. Mayers defends it nicely again.
It is short and around off again. Mayers punches it to mid off.
Drifts on the pads. Mayers clips it to square leg.
Again fires it fuller but down the leg side. Mayers tries to clip it but misses. Nurul Hasan dives and collects the ball in the second attempt, thinks about appealing but there was no bat.
This is another flatter one from Shakib, angling into middle, Mayers goes back and defends it.
Starts the new spell with a back-of-a-length delivery on off, Jermaine Blackwood defends it off the back foot.
Goes a tad fuller on off. Jermaine Blackwood pushes it towards covers this time.
Slightly shorter again, around off. Jermaine Blackwood punches it to point.
Lands on a length, on middle. Jermaine Blackwood nudges it to the leg side.
Goes fuller on off, Jermaine Blackwood drives but straight back to the bowler.
FOUR! Beautifully played! Khaled Ahmed goes a tad short outside off. Jermaine Blackwood waits for the ball to come, rides the bounce and then punches it through backward point for a boundary.
A flatter one, around off. Mayers defends it towards the off side.
Shakib Al Hasan is continuing with a flatter trajectory here, on off and Mayers blocks it out.
FOUR! Boundaries continue to flow! Short and wide outside off. Mayers cuts it and gets it in the gap through backward point for a boundary.
Shakib keeps it a tad short again but closer to off and Mayers defends it off the back foot.
Angles into leg. Mayers tries to clip it but misses. The ball brushes his pads and goes towards short fine leg. A leg bye is taken.
Shakib goes fuller on off. Jermaine Blackwood is solid in his front-foot defense.
Shortish length, outside off. Mayers rides the bounce and punches it to sweeper cover for a single.
On a length, on off. Jermaine Blackwood works it to short mid-wicket.

Goes fuller on off. Jermaine Blackwood drives it back to the bowler. Khaled Ahmed gets a fingertip to it as he tries to stop it in his follow-through. The ball goes on to hit the stumps at the bowler's end. There is an appeal for run out but Mayers is well inside his crease.
Goes fuller on off. Jermaine Blackwood drives it to mid off.
Lands on a length, on off. Jermaine Blackwood drives it back to the bowler.
Khaled Ahmed delivers it on a length and down the leg side. Jermaine Blackwood looks to flick it but does not connect.
Pitches it on off and it turns into middle and leg. Kyle Mayers works it to deep square leg for a single.
Slower through the air on middle. Jermaine Blackwood defends it towards the leg side.
On middle and fuller. Jermaine Blackwood defends it calmly again.
On the shorter side, outside off. Jermaine Blackwood punches it to sweeper cover for a single.
Pitches on middle and turns into Mayers. He works it towards the leg side.
200 up for West Indies! They trail by just 34 runs now! Fuller delivery on the pads. Mayers flicks it to deep square leg for a single.
Lands it full and on middle, Mayers defends it close to his front pad. The bowler appeals for an lbw, thinking it was pad first but nothing from the umpire.
Pitches it up and outside off, Mayers crunches his drive through cover-point and takes a single.
Fiery delivery, short and sliding down the leg side, Jermaine Blackwood tries glancing it off his hips but then pulls his bat back.
Lands it on a length and close to off, Jermaine Blackwood defends it close to his front off, off the inner edge.
Fullish and outside off, Jermaine Blackwood drives it powerfully towards mid off but fails to beat the fielder.
Short and outside off, some extra bounce, Blackwood leaps on the back foot and defends it down on the surface.
Around middle, on a shortish length, Mayers turns it through square leg for a single.
Short and wide outside off, Blackwood tries to cut but misses. The keeper appeals but nothing from the umpire.
Flighted and full outside off, Blackwood drives it to mid off.
Slower through the air, full and around off, Jermaine Blackwood pushes it to cover-point.

FOUR! Slapped! Shakib drags his length short and delivers it outside off, Jermaine Blackwood goes deep inside the crease and smashes it through cover-point. Chase is on as Mehidy Hasan runs after it but fails to pull it back in. Could have done better.
Flatter around the pads, defended on the leg side.
Khaled cooks a bouncer around off at 128 kph, and Mayers sways away from the line.
Fuller and around off, Mayers plays it down with soft hands to point and collects a single.
Digs it in short, wide outside off, Jermaine goes on his toes and cuts but fails to beat the diving point fielder.
Serves it on a length and around off, Jermaine Blackwood defends it off the front foot to mid on.
Around off, on a length, Blackwood keeps his weight on the back foot and punches it to covers.
Bangs it in short, around middle and leg, Jermaine Blackwood stands across and pulls it down to fine leg for one.
A dipping full toss on middle, it's pushed to mid off.
Turning down the leg side, it's worked behind square leg for a run.
Tossed up, around off, defended back to the bowler.
Quicker one, a slider on off, Mayers goes on the back foot and blocks.
Fuller this time, it's fired around middle and off, Mayers drives it towards the cover fielder.
Almost drags it on! Mehidy Hasan serves a slider around off, short in length and skidding into the batter, Mayers goes back to punch but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Khaled hurls across a half-tracker on off, some steep bounce there, Jermaine Blackwood goes on his back foot, jumps and defends it down.
Shortish again, outside off, this time, Blackwood hangs on the back foot and plays it down gently to point.

Four byes! Plenty of extras going West Indies' way. An attempted bouncer, a slower one, down the leg side, Blackwood leaves and it bounces in front of Nurul Hasan who fails to stop it. A boundary results at fine leg.
Yet another bouncer, around leg, Blackwood sways away and this time Nurul collects.
Khaled goes length, drops it around off, Jermaine is on the front foot as he defends.

Khaled steams in from 'round the wicket and cooks a very sharp bouncer. Around middle, Blackwood ducks at the last moment. Nurul Hasan jumps but fails to stop cleanly. They cross. It's also a no ball as this is the third bouncer over the head of the batter in this over.
Short in length and outside off, steered behind point for a single.
Turn and bounce outside off, Mayers tries to drive but misses.
Arm ball around off, it's defended off the back foot.
Fires it full and on middle, Mayers does well to defend it back towards the bowler.
Quicker one, around off, defended off the front foot.
Loopy and full, around off, Kyle Mayers defends it near his front pad.
Fullish and sliding down the leg side, it's clipped off the pads by Mayers but he finds the fielder at backward square leg.
The batter has just blocked that from his crease.
Back of a length, around off, Jermaine Blackwood remains on the back foot and works it through mid-wicket for two.
Extra bounce from a good length around off, Blackwood rises on the back foot to defend but it takes the inner edge and goes on one bounce over the stumps.
EDGY FOUR! Another well-directed short ball, around middle and leg, Jermaine Blackwood takes on the challenge to pull but it takes his gloves and flies behind the keeper for a boundary.
Bouncer on middle, JB ducks.
Drifting down the leg side, a touch short in length, Blackwood tries his best to glance but misses.
Short and wide outside off, Mayers leaves it alone.
Flatter and shorter outside off, left alone.
Slider around off, defended off the front foot.
A half-tracker outside off, Mayers cuts it through point for a brace.
Full and flighted outside off, Mayers drives it down to long off for a single.
Streaky! Loopy delivery, full and around leg, Blackwood kneels down to sweep but it takes the top edge and runs towards fine leg. The batters get two and the deficit now is just 7 runs.
FOUR! The fielder in the deep fails to pick it. Short in length and outside off, Mayers camps back and slaps it over backward point for a boundary. Fifty for Mayers, his third in Tests.
CENTURY STAND! Back of a length, around off, Mayers punches it firmly through point for a single. A very important partnership between the two!
Short and around leg, some uncomfortable extra bounce, Blackwood jumps and glances it down to long leg for a single.
Fuller and around middle, some late swing into the batter, Mayers defends it back to the bowler.
FOUR! BANG! West Indies move into the lead. Short in length and around off, Kyle Mayers hangs on the back foot and whacks it to the cover region for a cracking boundary.
Overpitches outside off, Mayers leans forward and drills his drive to the left of the deep point fielder. A brace is taken. 12 from the over, West Indies lead by 5 runs.
Turning down the leg side, Blackwood lets it be.
Fires it full and on middle, it's defended back.
Slower through the air, full and flighted outside off, Blackwood latches onto it and drives it through covers. Khaled uses his right boot to stop the ball and saves one run.
Tossed up, around off, defended off the front foot to the off side.
Flatter and shorter, around off, Mayers moves inside the crease and strokes it through covers. Two more.
Around off, flatter through the air, Mayers defends it back watchfully.
Flighted and full, around off, it's defended off the front foot to covers.
Loopy around off, another defensive shot off the front foot by Jermaine.
Quicker this time, around off and skidding in, Blackwood goes back and defends.
Flatter and shorter on off, blocked from the back foot.

What was that? Shakib attempts to dig it in short, but he drops that in his own half. The ball reaches the batter on a couple of bounces. It's going down, Blackwood tries to slog but misses. It's called a no ball.
Around middle, flatter and shorter, it's worked in front of square leg for one.
Shortish and on off, punched from the back foot to covers.
Flighted and on middle, Blackwood eases it down to mid on and scampers across to the other end.
Fuller and around leg, Mayers pushes it back towards the bowler.
Around leg, Mayers helps it off the inner half to square leg.
Flighted and on middle, turning away with some extra bounce, Mayers controls well and guides it towards point for one.
Loopy and full, around off, Blackwood leans forward and defends it to the off side.
Slightly short, around off and spinning in, Jermaine Blackwood goes back and helps it towards mid-wicket. That will be Tea on Day 2.
A flatter one and slightly shorter on off, Mayers goes back and blocks it.
Shakib goes fuller on off. Mayers gets well forward and defends it.
Hasan with a flatter delivery on off again. Mayers with a solid block.
Pushes it quicker, around off again. Mayers is ready to defend it yet again.
Shakib is not ready to give any flight and bowls it flatter again on off. Mayers defends it off the front foot.
Pitches it on off and it turns back in slightly. Mayers defends it off the inside half of his blade towards the leg side.
On middle and flatter. Jermaine Blackwood with a front-foot defense.
This is fuller and around leg. Jermaine Blackwood looks to sweep it but does not connect.
Goes fuller on off. Jermaine Blackwood blocks it out.

OUT! LBW! Mehidy Hasan strikes in his first over after Tea. Just what Bangladesh needed and Jermaine Blackwood, who was looking so good before Tea, departs early in this session. This is flatter and slightly shorter on middle. Jermaine Blackwood goes back and looks to work it towards the leg side. However, he misses it and the ball hits his pads. There is a huge appeal and the umpire raises his finger. Blackwood reviews it. The UltraEdge shows no bat involved and the Ball Tracking shows that it is hitting the stumps. The century stand is broken.
Howout: lbw b Mehidy Hasan

Commentary: Fuller delivery on middle. Joshua Da Silva blocks it out.
Shorter in length and turning into the batter. Joshua Da Silva goes back and defends it.
Tossed up on off. Mayers tries to defend but gets an inside edge onto his pads.
On middle and Mayers blocks it out.
A fuller delivery on middle. Mayers works it to mid on.
Tossed up nicely on middle. Mayers works it to mid-wicket this time.
Slower through the air on off. Mayers blocks it out.
Slightly shorter on off. Mayers blocks it off the back foot.
Tossed up on off. Joshua Da Silva gets forward to defend it.
Slower through the air on off. Joshua Da Silva is solid in his defense.
Fuller on middle. Joshua Da Silva blocks it out.
This is slightly shorter on off. Joshua Da Silva defends it towards the off side.
Tossed up on off. Defended off the front foot.
Goes shorter on off. Joshua Da Silva is right behind it to block it.
Fires it full and around off, Mayers flicks it to mid-wicket.
Leans forward to a full ball and jams it down safely.
Sliding down around leg, Mayers goes back and flicks it to square leg.
Too full and around off, Mayers mistimes his drive to covers.
Loopy and full, around off, Mayers drives but finds mid off this time.
Tossed up on off. Mayers tries to hit it away down the ground. The ball goes towards mid off. Shoriful Islam misfields and a single is taken.

That single brings up 250 for the West Indies! Another misfield this time from the bowler. Tossed up on off. Mayers drives it back to the bowler. Hasan fails to collect it cleanly and a single is taken.
Tossed up again on off. Joshua Da Silva pushes it to mid on.
Good running! This is tossed up on off again. Joshua Da Silva pushes it to mid on and sets off for a single. The fielder there fails to collect it cleanly and a single is completed.
A fuller one on off. Mayers drives it to covers.
Slower through the air, on off. Mayers blocks it out.
Pushes it quicker but the same line again. Mayers is solid in his front-foot defense.
Ohh...that was close! An arm ball, around off. It comes in with the angle and Joshua Da Silva leaves it. That was inches away from the off pole.
On middle and slower through the air. Joshua Da Silva works it towards mid-wicket.
Drifting on the pads. Joshua Da Silva clips it past square leg for a couple.
On middle and fuller again. Joshua Da Silva works it to short mid-wicket.
Pushes it quicker and angles it on middle again. Joshua Da Silva nudges it towards the leg side.
Tossed-up delivery on off. Joshua Da Silva gets a good stride forward and blocks it out.
Pitches it around leg. Mayers defends it off the front foot.
Almost the same line and Mayers gets to the pitch of the ball to defend it.
This is on off. Mayers defends it again off the front foot.
Slower through the air, on off. Mayers pushes it towards covers.
Shout for a catch, the umpire shakes his head. No review is taken. Flighted and around leg, Mayers tries to defend but misses. It goes off his pads to first slip.
Risky leave, this! Mehidy Hasan pitches it on off and the ball turns away a bit. Kyle Mayers leaves it trusting on the turn Mehidy will get.
Flatter and fuller on middle, defended back.
Short and around off, Joshua gets back and works it to square leg.
Leans forward to a full ball and blocks it to the off side.
Slower through the air, short and outside off, Joshua Da Silva punches it to covers.
Fuller and outside off, Da Silva drives it to cover-point.
Nicely floated, full and on off, Joshua Da Silva presses forward and defends. They are rushing through their overs.
Flighted and on off, Kyle defends it by getting forward.
Fuller and on off, driven firmly off the front foot to covers.
Too full again, but around leg, Mayers knocks it down to long on for a single.
Quicker off spinner on middle, Joshua Da Silva defends it from the back foot.
Extra airtime to this delivery, around off, Joshua Da Silva prefers to block it from the back foot.
Beats the bat! Drifting in close to off, Joshua Da Silva tries to defend the line but it straightens to beat the outside edge.
Flatter and fuller, around off, Mayers is on the front foot as he defends.
Fuller again, around leg, Mayers flicks but finds short mid-wicket.
Quicker and on middle, Mayers moves back and wrists it to mid-wicket again.
Very full this time, around middle, it's been pushed down to long on for a run.
Skidding down the leg side, Joshua gets some bat behind it and sends it down to fine leg. The fielder chases it down and they take three runs.
Flatter ball, around off, blocked safely from the back foot.
Spinning down the leg side, Joshua Da Silva flicks but it hits the short leg fielder.
Full and flighted on off, defended back off the front foot.
A touch short and on off, this time the batter defends it from the back foot.
Short again, around off, Joshua Da Silva hangs back and punches it to mid-wicket.
Flatter through the air, outside off and short once more, Joshua Da Silva is at ease in defending it down.
Loopy delivery, full and outside off, Joshua Da Silva lunges and defends it to safety. So in the last 32 minutes or so, Bangladesh have fired in 12 overs.
Drags it on, nearly. Full in length and outside off, Mayers tries to drive but it takes the inner edge and rolls on the leg side.
Lands it on a good length, outside off and going straight on, Mayers covers his stumps and shoulders arms.
Shoriful bowls it on a good length outside off, Kyle gets forward to push inside the line and runs it down off the outer edge to third man. They take two.
Width there outside off, short in length, Mayers rocks back and slams it over covers. The point fielder cuts it off running across to his left and they get three runs.
Around off, on a length, Joshua stays watchful on the back foot and defends it to the off side.
On a length and outside off, angling away, Joshua Da Silva shoulders arms.
Too full in length and on middle, Mayers hits it firmly down to long on for a run.
Very full again, as it's fired on middle, Joshua Da Silva pushes it down to mid on.
Loopy this time, full and around off, Joshua Da Silva presses forward and defends it to the off side.
Stays on the back foot to a short ball and works it in front of square leg.
Quicker through the air, full and on off, Joshua Da Silva defends it from the back foot.
Flatter again, on off, defended from the back foot.
Outside off, tapped down to point for a run.
Fuller and outside off, Joshua Da Silva mistimes his drive to mid off.
On a good length around middle, staying down, Da Silva defends it to mid-wicket.
Outside off, no shot offered.
That is defended solidly off the front foot.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
FOUR! Shot! Full and flighted outside off, Mayers takes a good stride forward and bludgeons his drive through covers for a boundary.
Fullish and around leg, flicked across the line but straight to short leg.
Floated one, full and around leg, it's defended down on the surface.
Slightly short and outside off, Mayers plays a controlled square cut to point.
Short and on off, punched to deep point for a single.
Flighted around off, full and going straight on, rather than coming forward, Joshua Da Silva defends it from the back foot.
FOUR! Streaky! Short in length, outside off, extra pace and bounce there for Khaled, Mayers throws his bat at it and the outside edge flies over the slip cordon for a boundary.
Khaled goes length and delivers it on middle and leg, Kyle defends it by getting half-forward.
Around leg, landing on a length and skidding off the surface, Mayers is caught on the back foot, attempting to flick but misses. There is a shout for an lbw, not given. Perhaps, pitching outside leg.
Identical to the last delivery, this time Mayers uses his bat and defends it on the leg side.

EDGY FOUR! Mayers is taking a lot of risk at the moment and it's paying off as well. This one is on a length and outside off, Mayers goes for a drive through the line but it takes the outside edge and flies wide of second slip. He moves to 84!
Fullish and around off, Mayers pushes it firmly to covers.
Floated delivery, landing full and around off, Joshua Da Silva lunges and defends.
Fuller again, around middle, pushed down to mid on.
Spinning down the leg side, the batter offers no shot and pads it away.
Tossed up, around off, Da Silva defends it from the back foot.
Drags his length short, around off, Joshua pulls but finds the mid-wicket fielder.
Flighted and full, around off, Joshua Da Silva continues to defend from the back foot.
On a length, around off, Kyle defends it from the back foot to covers.
A touch short and on middle, Mayers sticks on the back foot and blocks it towards mid off.
FOUR! Sumptuous looking shot! Back of a length, around off, Kyle Mayers camps back and sweetly punches it through covers for a boundary.
On middle, a length ball, Mayers drops it with gentle hands to covers and pinches a single. Moves to 89!
Shortish and outside off, Joshua remains on the back foot and pushes it to covers.
Angles it in, on a good length around middle, staying low, Joshua Da Silva does well to keep it out towards square leg.
Fuller and on middle, Mayer lunges and defends it to mid on.
Drifting down the leg side, Kyle helps it to square leg and collects a single. Lead is 50 runs now.
Loopy and full, outside off, Da Silva presses forward and defends.
Quicker and full,  on middle, defended from the back foot.
Too full and on off, Joshua Da Silva pushes it down to mid on.
Slider around off, a bit on the shorter side, Joshua Da Silva has no qualms in blocking it off the back foot.
Serves it full and around off, Mayers drives it through the line and Shakib at covers makes a partial stop diving across to his right. They take a run.
FOUR! Boom! Short in length and outside off, Joshua rocks on the back foot and thwacks it through cover-point for a boundary. He has sized up the conditions well now.
Fine shot! Fuller in length and outside off, Joshua doesn't try to hit it hard and only creams his drive past mid off. Two runs are taken.
A dipping yorker around off, Joshua Da Silva keeps his eyes glued to the ball and digs it out from the bottom half of his blade.
On a length and outside off, Da Silva defends it solidly off the back foot.
Fuller in length and outside off, Joshua Da Silva plays a confident drive but finds the mid off fielder.
A fullish delivery on off. Mayers drives it firmly towards mid off.

In the air...but it lands safely! Islam with a fullish length again, outside off. Mayers looks to go over the top. However, it takes the upper half of his blade and clears the cover fielder. He takes two runs.
FOUR! Lovely shot! Full delivery on off. Mayers drives it through extra cover for a boundary.

SIX! Wow, what a shot to bring your second Test hundred! The first time he got that was against the same team on his debut and he converted that into a double century. Looking good to do the same again. Short delivery on middle, Mayers comes up with a short-arm jab and sends it flying over square leg for a biggie. The most impressive thing about this knock is that he came in when his team was under some serious pressure, he weathered the storm and is now cashing in!
Loose shot! Short and wide outside off. Mayers looks to cut but misses.
On a length, on off. Mayers blocks it out.
FOUR! Wonderful shot from Joshua Da Silva now! Khaled Ahmed drifts on the pads. Joshua Da Silva flicks it through square leg for a boundary. Bangladesh feeling the heat here!
Lands on a length, on off. Joshua Da Silva blocks it out solidly.
On a length, on middle. Joshua Da Silva clips it to fine leg for a single.
On a length, on off. Mayers pushes it through covers for a single. The lead is now 75!
Goes fuller on off. Joshua Da Silva drives it straight to mid off.
On a length, on middle. Joshua Da Silva nudges it towards mid-wicket.
A fuller and flatter delivery on off. Mayers pushes it gently towards covers for a single.
Angling into leg. Joshua Da Silva skips down the track and works it towards mid-wicket.
This is fuller on middle. Joshua Da Silva drives it to mid on.
Appeal for an LBW but a clear inside edge there! On off and coming through with the angle. Joshua Da Silva looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto his pads.
On off and fuller. Blocked off the front foot.
Slower through the air, on off. Joshua Da Silva pushes it to covers.
Lands on a length, around off. Mayers punches it through covers for a single.
Serves a length delivery, outside off. Joshua Da Silva pushes it through cover-point and takes a single. He looks for the second run but decides against it in the end.
Back of a length, around off. Mayers dabs it towards point.
Goes fuller and down the leg side. Mayers looks to flick it but misses. The ball brushes his pads and goes towards the keeper on the bounce.
Top delivery! Angles a good-length delivery, around off. Mayers looks to punch it away but misses.
Goes a tad fuller on off. Mayers tries to drive it away but gets an inside edge onto his pads.
Fires this one on middle. Joshua Da Silva blocks it off the back foot.
Goes fuller on middle and leg. Joshua Da Silva works it towards the leg side.
This is pitched up on middle. Joshua Da Silva drives it to mid on.
Angles it on leg. Joshua Da Silva flicks it to square leg.
Drifting on leg again. Joshua Da Silva looks to sweep it but does not get a proper connection.
Another flatter and quicker one on middle. Joshua Da Silva pushes it to mid on.

Ebadot Hossain has troubled Mayers in the last few deliveries! Back of a length, outside off. Mayers tries to punch it away but gets the inside edge. The ball goes past the stumps towards fine leg for a single.

A review for a caught behind! The original decision is NOT OUT! It will remain not out as the UltraEdge shows no bat is involved. Coming to the ball - It is full and outside off. Joshua Da Silva looks to drive away from his body but misses. There is an appeal but the umpire is not interested. Shakib takes a review more in hope and it eventually results in Bangladesh losing a review.
On a length, on middle. Joshua Da Silva clips it to square leg.
On a length, on off. Joshua Da Silva blocks it off the front foot.
On a length, around off. It keeps a bit low but Joshua Da Silva gets his bat down in time.
Lands on a length, outside off. Joshua Da Silva steers it through the gully region for a couple.
Tossed up on off. Mayers blocks it off the front foot.
This is fuller on leg. Mayers sweeps it towards deep backward square leg for a single.
Tossed up on off. Joshua Da Silva drives it to mid on.
Slower through the air, on off. Joshua Da Silva is well forward to block it.
This is fuller again, on off. Joshua Da Silva drives but finds the mid off fielder.
Slightly shorter in length, on middle. Joshua Da Silva works it past square leg for a couple.
FOUR! Great timing from Mayers! Fullish delivery on off. Mayers leans forward and drives it beautifully through the extra cover region for a boundary.
Ebadot Hossain responds with a good yorker, right in the blockhole. However, Mayers digs it out without much fuss.
A full delivery angling into leg. Mayers flicks it towards deep square leg for a couple.
Back of a length, on off. Mayers rides the bounce and blocks it out.
On the shorter side again angling into the body. Mayers works it to deep backward square leg for a single.
This is full and outside off. Joshua Da Silva drives but gets an outside edge. However, the ball falls just short of the diving keeper.
Tossed up on off. Mayers drives it to long off for a single.
This is flatter on off. Joshua Da Silva blocks it off the front foot.
Slower through the air and around off. Joshua Da Silva works it to mid on.
Slightly shorter on middle. Joshua Da Silva works it to square leg.
Keeps it a tad short again on middle. Joshua Da Silva blocks it off the back foot.
Fuller on off. Joshua Da Silva drives but finds the mid off fielder.
On middle and fuller. Mayers gets a good stride forward and blocks it.
Tossed up, on off. Mayers gets to the pitch of the ball by advancing and blocks it out.
On middle and turning into Mayers. He works it to deep square leg for a couple. Good running!
On the shorter side. It pitches around off and turns in with good bounce. Mayers plays it quite well as he pushes it square of the wicket on the off side for a single.
A fuller delivery on middle. Joshua Da Silva clips it to mid-wicket.
Tad shorter, angling into middle. Joshua Da Silva works it towards the leg side again.
Angling into leg. Mayers works it to fine leg for a single.
Pushes it quicker on middle. Joshua Da Silva blocks it off the front foot.
Tad short on off and Joshua Da Silva gets right back to block it.
Tossed up on middle. This time Joshua Da Silva is well forward to defend it.
Slightly quicker and a tad shorter. Joshua Da Silva nudges it towards the leg side.
Keeps it shorter again, on off. Joshua Da Silva uses the depth of the crease and pushes it to mid off.
FOUR! Exceptional shot! Shorter length on middle. Mayers goes back and punches it through covers for a boundary. Lead is now 100.
Tossed up on off. Mayers skips down the track and hits it hard towards sweeper cover for a single.
Slower through the air on middle. Joshua Da Silva defends it off the inside half of his blade and the ball goes just to the left of the diving short leg fielder.
Tossed up on off. Blocked off the front foot.
Goes shorter on middle. Joshua Da Silva defends it off the back foot this time.
FOUR! Angling into leg. Joshua Da Silva sweeps and sweeps it well towards the fine leg fence. Boundaries keep coming at regular intervals!
A flatter one on off. Mayers blocks it out.
Slightly shorter on off. Mayers pushes it towards the off side.
Nicely flighted delivery, around off. Mayers drives it towards the point fielder.
Quicker delivery on off. Mayers pushes it back to the bowler.
Short and wide outside off. Mayers cuts it to deep point for a single.
Mehidy Hasan bowls it a bit quicker and it is slightly shorter on off. Joshua Da Silva gets back and defends it towards the off side. That will be Stumps on Day 2!
Mayers is up and running on Day 3! Length and on off. He taps it to covers for a quick single.
On a length and on middle. Da Silva blocks it towards mid on.
An appeal for LBW but nothing given. Height was an issue. Length ball, around off, it nips back in. Da Silva looks to defend but gets beaten on the inside edge and gets hit high on the pads.
This is outside off, it is pushed to covers.
This one stays low! Length ball, outside off. Da Silva dabs it with soft hands and it goes off the outside edge past first the slip cordon for a single.
Dot ball to end the over! Length ball, just outside off. Mayers punches it to cover-point.
A flighted delivery, too full and on off. Da Silva blocks it out.
Tight from Hasan! Tossed up on off. Da Silva defends on the back foot.
Flatter and around off. Da Silva pushes it to the left of Hasan who gets low and stops it.
Slightly shorter and outside off. Da Silva cuts it late, past point for a couple of runs.

OUT! LBW! Bangladesh get early success on Day 3! Just what they needed and they break this stubborn partnership! Hasan gets good amount of drift this time, this is flighted fuller and around off. Joshua Da Silva pre-meditates and looks to sweep but picks the wrong line and gets hit on the pads. An appeal for LBW and up goes the finger. It looked plumb and Joshua Da Silva walks back shaking his head. Good start for Bangladesh!
Howout: lbw b Mehidy Hasan

Commentary: Full and on off. Blocked on the front foot.
Fuller ball, around leg. Mayers looks to work on the leg side but gets an inside edge. An appeal but there was clear edge.
Good bounce this time! The bowlers are getting good purchases early on! Bangladesh will hope to make inroads! Short of a length and on leg. Mayers misses his flick and gets hit on the pads.
On a length and outside off. Mayers pushes through covers for a single.
Joseph is off the mark! Length ball, outside off. Joseph punches off the back foot through covers for a brace.
Four byes! Bangs a bouncer on middle. Joseph leaves it. It is too high for the keeper to get his mitts on and it races behind for a boundary. 350 up for West Indies, they now lead by 117 runs.
On off, pushed straight to mid off.
FOUR! Loosener! Slides it down the leg side. Mayers sweeps it behind square on the leg side for a boundary.
On middle, blocked out.
FOUR! A full ball, slanting around off. Mayers drives it firmly through covers for a boundary. The ground is slow due to overnight rain but it was hit cleanly.
Full and on off. Mayers defends on the front foot.
Tossed up on off. Mayers steps across and keeps it out.
Short but wide outside off. Left alone.
Hits the hard length, outside off, Joseph punches it to covers.
Length and on off, pushed to covers again.
FOUR! Good shot from Joseph! On a length and on middle. Joseph hangs back and lofts it over mid on for a boundary.
On a length and on top of off. Joseph punches off the back foot but straight to covers.

OUT! CAUGHT! Bangladesh gets another one! Joseph goes now! Ahmed drags his length ball and bowls it short and tailing on leg. Joseph is a bit hurried as he looks to pull and he mistimes his shot to mid-wicket where Liton Das takes it with ease.
Howout: c Litton Das b Khaled Ahmed

Commentary: FOUR! Good follow-up delivery but the result is an unfortunate boundary! A length ball, on off, stays low. Roach looks to defend but gets a thick outside edge past the slip cordon and into the third man fence.
Shorter and outside off, cut to deep point for a run.
On middle, blocked out.
Two leg byes! Angling on the pads, Roach tickles it to fine leg for leg bye as it goes off the pads.
Tossed up on middle. Roach blocks it on the front foot.
Shorter and sliding down. Roach looks to flick it but misses.
Short and this time wide of off. Kemar plays it to point.
Length and on off. Mayers blocks it on the off side.
An off-cutter, this lands on off and moves away. Mayers looks to pull but misses.
Length ball, outside off. Mayers knocks it to deep point for a single.
Length ball, drifting on the pads. Roach fends it away on the leg side.
On middle, tucked to mid-wicket this time.
Touch fuller and on off. Roach defends it to point.
A loopy ball, outside off and spinning away. Mayers punches it to deep point for a single.
Shorter and outside off. Roach slaps it through covers for a single.
Hasan gets drift again! this one lands around leg and it spins on middle, bounce there as well. Mayers misses his block and gets hit on the pads.
Tossed up, on off, pushed to point.
Floated, full and outside off. Kept out.
Darted on the pads. Mayers looks to flick it away but misses and gets hit on the pads.
Length and on middle. Roach solidly blocks it.
Outside off, on a length. Roach guides it to point.
A bumper around middle. Roach sits under it.
Short in length and outside off. It climbs on Roach who dabs it past backward point for a couple of runs. Slow surface there.
Outside off. Left alone.
Outside off again, this one stays low. Roach shoulders arms to it.
Too full and on off. Defended out.
Flatter, outside off, turning more away. Mayers lets it go.
Quicker one now, on off. Worked to long off for a single.
Tossed up on middle. Blocked out.
Another solid block from Roach.
Quicker, fuller and on off. Roach rocks back and makes another solid block.
Starts off with a shortish ball over off stump. Kyle Mayers hops back to keep it down on the off side.
Fuller and wider, this is driven to deep point for a single.
Pitched up this time, on the fifth stump line. Kemar Roach lets it through to the keeper.
Banged in short around leg stump, Roach ducks under it well.
Ahmed keeps it on a shorter length and angles it onto the body. Roach nudges it out on the leg side.
Full and close to the off pole, just shaping in a touch. Kemar Roach makes an assured leave.
FOUR! Floats it up on off stump, Kyle Mayers plays a lovely flowing cover drive and picks up a boundary.
Flatter and around the pads, tucked away towards mid-wicket for one.
Slower through the air but spilled well down the leg side.
A bit quicker, around off. Roach keeps it out on the off side.
Drifted onto the pads, Roach works it behind square on the leg side for a couple of runs. West Indies now lead by 150 runs!
Shorter and down leg, Roach doesn't play at it.

OUT! CAUGHT! The slower ball has done the trick for Khaled Ahmed and he gets the big fish. This is a bit fuller and around middle and leg, the pace is taken off the ball. The ball just sticks a bit in the surface and Kyle Mayers is caught on the crease. Mayers is too early in his drive and ends up chipping it to the left of mid on. Shoriful Islam slides in and holds onto the catch. Mayers departs after a big innings and Bangladesh will now look to wrap up the innings at the earliest.
Howout: c Shoriful Islam b Khaled Ahmed

Commentary: A huge appeal from the keeper for caught behind but that's all it is. Back of a length, around off. The ball zips through a bit off the surface and goes past the outside edge. The replay shows that Anderson Phillip didn't get an edge on that one.
Full and around off, left alone by Phillip.
Ahmed tries to bowl full and attack the pads but spills it down the leg side.
This is angled into middle, Phillip flicks it towards short mid-wicket.
Full and straight, firmly driven towards mid on. A wicket-maiden then for Khaled Ahmed.
On a length, turning in from the off pole. Kemar Roach stays solid in defense.
On off, Roach strides forward to defend.
Tossed up a bit this time, around off. Roach blocks it out.
Slower and shorter, on off. Kemar Roach goes on the back foot to defend it out.
Turning into the pads, Roach knocks it 'round the corner for a single.
Floated up, on middle and leg. Anderson Phillip lunges forward to defend.

Full and just sliding down the leg side. Kemar Roach looks to flick but misses and there's a stifled appeal for caught behind. The fielder at short leg wants a review but Shakib Al Hasan isn't interested and the replay shows why.
Full and straight, Roach does well to get his bat down in time.
Back of a length, around off. Roach taps it towards cover.
On a good length and over off, Roach hops on the back foot to keep it out.
This is angled onto the pads, Roach tries to flick it away but can't get it through.
Full and on leg stump, Roach clips it leg side but can't get it past mid-wicket. Maiden!
Nicely flighted, outside off. Phillip strides forward to make the block.
Mehidy Hasan switches to around the wicket and tosses it up on middle. Anderson Phillip plays an uppish on drive and gets it through wide mid on for a single.
Beaten! This is just drifted across the right-hander from around the wicket. Roach looks to defend but gets beaten past the outside edge.
On leg stump, Roach defends it out.
Quicker through the air, around leg. Kemar Roach makes a solid defensive block.
A tad shorter and on leg stump, Roach goes deep in his crease to nudge it leg side.
Close but not close enough! On a hard length, close to the off pole. The ball just doesn't rise up at all on this occasion and Anderson Phillip is beaten all ends up.
Length again, around off, Phillip keeps it out on the leg side.
Good-length delivery, over middle. Phillip pushes it out off the back foot.
Well short! Pitched up, around off. Anderson Phillip looks to take it on and loft it over mid off but mistimes it horribly as the ball falls well short of the man at mid off.
Variable bounce again! Length ball, around the top of off but the ball stays real low once again. Phillip does well to get his bat down in time.
FOUR! Glorious shot from Anderson Phillip and that's his first boundary in Test cricket. Overpitched, around off, Phillip drives it past the man at mid off and the ball goes into the fence.
FOUR! Valuable runs here for West Indies and they will take it. Half-volley, wide of off and Kemar Roach creams it through cover-point for a boundary.
Much better from Islam. Top of off line, Roach blocks it out.
Length again, on off, Roach plays it towards mid off.
Good short ball, banged in around leg stump. Roach ducks under it well.
A touch fuller and slanted across the right-hander. Kemar Roach watches it go past him and into the mitts of the keeper.
Short again, this time around off. Roach sways away from the line of the ball.
Pitches it up, around off but it is the slower delivery. Phillip blocks it off the front foot.
Leg bye! This is short and at the body, Anderson Phillip tries to fend it off awkwardly. The ball goes off his hips and towards backward square leg. They get a leg bye.
Short of a good length, at the stumps. Roach defends it out.
Full and straight, pushed back towards the bowler.
FOUR! Cracking shot! Length ball, outside off. Kemar Roach stands tall and drives through the line of the ball, dispatching it into the cover fence.
Length again, this time on a tighter line, Roach makes the leave.
Around the top of off, angling across the batter. Anderson Phillip is a bit late but manages to defend it out.
A length ball, on middle, kept out by Phillip.
Switches to around the wicket now and angles it on the body, Phillip nudges it out on the leg side.

EDGED AND FOUR! Good length, outside off. Anderson Phillip takes a step forward and throws his bat at it. The ball goes off the top edge and flies over the slip cordon running away into the fence. 400 is up now for West Indies.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Brilliant comeback delivery from Shoriful Islam, goes a bit fuller and angles it in closer to the off pole. Anderson Phillip opts to drive at it with a straight bat but seems to have got beaten past the outside edge. Appeal for a caught behind...not given! The keeper seems interested and Shakib Al Hasan does go upstairs. The replay shows that it is close to the bat and UltraEdge confirms there is a faint edge. OUT!
Howout: c Nurul Hasan b Shoriful Islam

Commentary: Full and on the pads, flicked away to fine leg for a single. The lead now grows to 170.
FOUR! Nicely done in the end by Jayden Seales. This is very full and on off, Seales squeezes it out with soft hands and the ball runs away through the vacant backward point region for a boundary.
Around the top of off, kept out on the off side by Seales.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Jubilation for Khaled Ahmed as he gets his maiden five-wicket haul in Test cricket. Lovely delivery this, around the top of off and just shaping away a touch after pitching. Jayden Seales has a little dab at it and gets the outside edge. Nurul Hasan dives down to his left to take a good catch. West Indies bowled out for 408 and they lead by 174 runs!
Howout: c Nurul Hasan b Khaled Ahmed

Commentary: Bangladesh and Iqbal are off the mark! A length ball, outside off. Iqbal punches off the back foot to deep point for a single.
A length ball, outside off. Joy steps a bit across and blocks it back to Roach.
Roach steams in and serves a short ball, outside off. Joy watchfully leaves it alone.
A length ball, around off, this one nips back in sharply. Joy hangs back and tucks it to square leg.
Short of a length and around off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy keeps it out.
This one shapes away but the line was outside off. Joy makes an easy leave.
A length ball, angling across, outside off. Iqbal defends it inside the line and against the angle.

Overthrow! A length ball on middle. Iqbal tucks it to mid-wicket and calls for a quick single. He rushes across and the fielder has a shy at the bowler's end but misses. The ball probably brushed Iqbal and goes away for a single.
On a length ball, outside off. Iqbal punches it wide of mid off for a single.
This is way down the leg side. Joy lets it through.
Short of a length and around off, nips away. Joy taps it to point.
Length ball, way outside off. Joy leaves it alone for the keeper to collect.
Outside off, left alone.
Short in length and outside off. Iqbal shoulders arms to it.
Good delivery but Roach can get tighter! A full ball, outside off and nips away off the deck. Iqbal lets it go.

OUT! EDGED AND GONE! 250 wickets for Kemar Roach in Test cricket! Not a good shot from Iqbal though! He could have left it alone! Roach bowls a full ball, angling just outside off and makes it to shape away. Iqbal is tempted for a big-booming drive but gets an outside edge and Joshua Da Silva pouches it. He celebrates with his teammates and waves the ball towards the pavilion.
Howout: c Joshua Da Silva b Kemar Roach

Commentary: Another nut from Roach! Angles it full and this one straightens up! it is near around off and Shanto makes a sharp leave.
Length and outside off. Left alone.
Length ball, tailing on the pads. Joy misses his flick and gets hit on the pads. It was going down.
Way outside off, on a length Joy shoulders arms.
Tailing on the pads, it is flicked to deep square leg for a single.
Short in length and angling across. Shanto looks to pull but misses.
A full toss on middle. Shanto flicks it to short leg where Raymon Reifer makes a good stop.
Length ball, going across, outside off. Shanto offers no shot.
Length ball, around off. Joy defends to covers on the front foot.
EDGED AND FOUR! A sharp bouncer, slanting around off. Joy is not fully into this shot as he tries to dab it away but gets an outside edge and it lobs over the slip cordon for a boundary.
Length ball, outside off. Joy blocks it very late and on the off side.
This one is at 133 kph, on middle. Joy defends on the back foot. No ball called for overstepping.
A length ball, outside off, slightly comes back in. Joy defends off the inner half and on the deck.
A huge appeal for LBW but that might be just missing the leg pole! A length ball, around middle and it jags back in sharply. Joy is beaten by the seam and gets rapped on the pads.
On middle, blocked out.
A length ball, this is slanted well across the left-hander. Shanto leaves it alone.
Length again, in that channel around off. Najmul Hossain Shanto makes a watchful leave.
Almost chops it on! Back of a length, around off. Shanto looks to defend off the back foot but gets a bottom edge back onto the deck. Luckily for him, the ball hits his pads and not the stumps.
Length again, on off, blocked out.
Good carry through! On a good length, on the fourth stump line and just zipping past the outside edge of Shanto's willow.
FOUR! Overpitched and punished! Full and around off, Najmul Hossain Shanto with a lovely straight drive back past the bowler and into the long off fence.
FOUR! A bit too straight on this occasion from Kemar Roach. A half-volley on the pads and this is clipped past square leg for a boundary.
FOUR! Three boundaries on the trot now for Bangladesh. A full toss, around off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy drills it past the man at silly mid off and into the fence.

OUT! TAKEN! Kemar Roach has the last laugh and picks up his second wicket early in the innings. This is on a perfect length, around off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy goes back and across looking to defend but gets the outside edge. Jermaine Blackwood takes a sharp catch at third slip around chest height and West Indies with another fast start here.
Howout: c Jermaine Blackwood b Kemar Roach

Commentary: Length again, close to the off pole. Anamul Haque makes an assured leave.
Probing line and length from Kemar Roach and he seems to be on song here. In that channel around off and just shaping away a touch. Haque has a poke at it but gets beaten past the outside edge.

Too close for comfort! Roach goes a bit wider of the crease and serves a big inswinger. Anamul Haque leaves but the ball just misses the off stump by a couple of inches. End of another successful over from Roach.
FOUR! Pitched up, around off. Najmul Hossain Shanto drives and drives well, gets it past the man at silly mid on and collects a boundary. Bangladesh now trail by 148 runs.
Good length, around middle and leg. Shanto hops and defends it out.
A bumper now, well-directed and over leg stump. Najmul Hossain Shanto ducks under it well.
Short of a good length, angled across the off stump. Shanto lets it through to the keeper.
Length and on the pads, this worked away towards mid-wicket for a single.
FOUR! Alzarri Joseph is just a bit too full and straight at the moment. On middle and leg, Anamul Haque drives it through wide mid on and picks up yet another boundary.
Comes from around the wicket and angles in a short ball at the body. The ball takes off after pitching and Shanto does well to sway away from the line of the ball.
A touch fuller and on middle, this is flicked away towards mid-wicket for one.
On a nagging length, around off. Haque leaves it alone and the ball swings in late.
Length this time, angling into middle and leg, Haque keeps it out.

OUT! LBW! Kemar Roach serves a length ball and the ball jags back in sharply from around off stump. Anamul Haque looks to work it leg side but misses and gets pinged on the front pad. Joshua Da Silva pouches the ball behind the stumps as well. The appeal though is for LBW and it is given! Anamul Haque reviews it straight away as he thinks it is a bit too high. UltraEdge shows that there's no bat involved and the Ball Tracking shows that the ball is clipping the top of middle and leg. The on-field decision will stay and with that, the rain has gotten heavier. Umpire Joel Wilson raises his finger while rushing back into the dressing room, a sight probably never seen before.
Howout: lbw b Kemar Roach

Commentary: Goes fuller and angles it in from outside off. Litton Das plays it with soft hands towards cover-point.
Starts off with a length ball, around middle. Shanto blocks it out from inside his crease.
Length again, on off. Najmul Hossain Shanto taps it towards cover and looks for the quick single but is sent back by his partner.
A touch fuller and on off, solidly defended off the front foot by Shanto.
This is pitched up, around off, Shanto drives but straight towards silly mid off.
Pitched up, in that channel around off. Shanto leaves it alone.
And again! Fuller and around off, Shanto shoulders his arms. Anderson Phillip starts his spell with a maiden.
A length ball, outside off. Das drops it through covers for a single. He is off the mark.
Fuller and on off. Shanto defends it solidly.
Angles a full ball on middle. Shanto is solid behind the line to defend.
Touch fuller and around off. Shanto tucks it off the inner half of the bat and to mid-wicket for a single.
Two runs! A length ball, outside off. Das punches it aerially and past point. The ball does not have legs to run away and the fielder cuts it off near the fence. Two.
Full and outside off, played back to the bowler.
Length ball, slanting across on off. Shanto taps it to covers and denies a quick single.
Dropped! A length ball, around off. Shanto tries to play straight drive but plays it uppishly and back to Phillip but it was too quick for him to show his reflexes.
FOUR! Good shot! A length ball, outside off. Shanto punches it very late and through gully for a boundary.
On the pads, flicked to deep square leg for one.
Around off on a length. Blocked out.
Overpitched and outside off. Das leans and drives it through covers for three runs as Kraigg Brathwaite chases the ball and saves a single.
Length and outside off. Left alone.
Tight from Roach! Slants a length ball on middle. Das is solid as he defends this.
Full and angling on middle. Das tries to flick it away but inner edges it behind square leg for a single.
On off, kept out.
Length ball, just around off, jags back in. Shanto is hurried as he blocks it out.

A huge, huge appeal for LBW but not given! West Indies do not review as well! They think height might be an issue! Roach slants a full ball, around middle and leg, there is steep bounce as well. Shanto looks to flick it but misses and gets hit on the pads. Ball Tracking later shows wickets were missing.
FOUR! Very full and tailing on the pads. Das helps it away to fine leg for a boundary.
On a length and on middle at 132 kph. Das turns it to square leg where the fielder dives to his right and stops it. One. 50 up...
Length and outside off. Left alone.
Another outside off delivery. Shanto shoulders arms.
On a length and just outside off. Blocked to covers.
Length ball, outside off. Shanto strokes it to covers.
A fuller ball, swinging in around off, Das pushes it to mid on.
Fullish delivery, wide of off. Das drives it through covers for a brace.
Hard length ball, outside off. Das lets it go.
Tad full and around middle and off. Das blocks it out on the leg side.
Length and outside off, nips in. Das looks to drive but mistimes it to mid-wicket. This is good from Roach.
Ends with a lovely delivery! A fuller ball, outside off. Das looks to drive it but misses.
Seales comes from around the wicket and serves a length ball around off. Shanto keeps it out on the off side.
A bit of a yes and no but no harm done. This is around off, Shanto taps it towards cover and looks for a single but sends his partner back in time.
Nice, probing line from Jayden Seales. Length again, angling in from outside off but the ball holds its line. Shanto makes the leave at the last second.
A touch fuller and on off, Shanto drives it back towards the bowler without any timing.
Gets the wide yorker in now, Najmul Hossain Shanto looks to squeeze it out but is beaten for pace.
Maiden! Close to the off pole and well left by Shanto.
Starts off with a length, outside off. Easy leave this time around for Litton Das.
Scrambled seam this time from Kyle Mayers, on a good length and on off. Das solidly blocks it out.
Around off, this is guided away towards point.
This is angled in fuller and into off, Das blocks it off the front foot.
Pitched up, on off. Litton Das stays solid in defense.
On a good length, over middle and leg, Das eases it out towards mid on. Maiden to start with from Kyle Mayers.
Full and outside off, just a bit too wide to entice the batter into playing the drive.
This is on a length and outside off, left alone by Shanto.
Pitched up on off, this is driven towards mid on.
Around the top of off, blocked out by Shanto.
Fuller in length and outside off, Najmul Hossain Shanto looks to cover drive but ends up dragging it towards mid on.
Good length, on the fourth stump line, Shanto leaves it alone. Another maiden over for Jayden Seales and West Indies.
Goes a bit fuller and bowls it on the fourth stump line. Litton Das lets it through to the keeper.
Mayers pushes it a bit wider and looks to swing it back in but Das just leaves it alone.
On off, Das stays solid in defense.
Risky single but it's well run in the end. Just short of a length and around off, Das drops it towards cover and sets off for a quick run.
Mayers angles it in from around the wicket and keeps it close to the off pole. Najmul Hossain Shanto makes a watchful leave.
Fuller and angling into middle, this one keeps a touch low. Shanto works it towards wide mid on.
Good length, around middle and leg. Litton Das goes on the front foot and presents a dead bat at it.

Half an appeal from the bowler for LBW but it seems too high. Good length again, around off and just nipping in a touch. Das looks to defend off the front foot but misses and gets struck on the pads. The replay shows that the ball was going well over the stumps.
FOUR! Full and drifting onto the pads, Litton Das clips it off his legs and past square leg for a boundary. Bangladesh now trail by 117 runs.
Just a tad shorter in length and around off. Das shoulders his arms at it.

OUT! LBW! Jayden Seales finds the right length this time and gets the ball to nip back in sharply from around the off stump. Litton Das is caught on the crease as he looks to play it on the leg side and the ball crashes into his pads, staying a bit low as well. A huge appeal for LBW but it is turned down! After a bit of a discussion, Kraigg Brathwaite does go for the review. UltraEdge shows that there's no bat involved and Ball Tracking comes up with three reds as the ball is going on to hit leg stump. Brilliant review from West Indies and they have the fourth wicket now.
Howout: lbw b Jayden Seales

Commentary: Jayden Seales welcomes Shakib Al Hasan to the crease with a sharp bouncer. This is bowled from around the wicket and angled in over leg stump. Shakib does well to duck under it.
Leg bye! Short of a length, angling on the hips. Shanto misses his tuck and gets hit on the body. It rolls to square leg for a leg bye.
Fuller and outside off. Shakib punches it through point for a single.

Good delivery! A length ball, nipping back in from around off. Shanto is squared up as he looks to defend and he manages an outside edge to the right of third slip where Nkrumah Bonner dives low to his right to collect on a bounce.
FOUR! Too full and on off. Shanto on drives it to long on for a boundary.
FOUR! Carbon copy by Shanto! Fuller again, around off. Shanto drives it past the non-strikers end stumps and to long on for a boundary.
Touch fuller and on middle, eased to mid on.
Short of a length and outside off. Shakib tries to cut on the up but mistimes it to point for a single.
Four byes! This is full and sliding down the leg side. Shanto misses his flick and it goes past the keeper and to the fine leg fence.
Superb delivery! This one straightens up off the deck, on a length and on leg. Shanto fails to play it out and gets hit high on the pads.
A yorker now, widish one. Shanto jams it out on the off side.
A bouncer now, it climbs more. Shanto sits under it.
Outside off, on a length. Shanto leaves it alone.
On a length and outside off. Al Hasan drops it to point for a single.
Length ball, outside off, nipping slightly in. Shanto thinks to play at it but withdraws his bat quickly.
Full and on off. Blocked out.
Short of a length and on off. Shanto anticipated that a bouncer was incoming and he ducks under it.
FOUR! This time Najmul Hossain Shanto was ready to play the short one as he gets on top of the bounce and pulls it to deep square leg for a boundary.
Full and just outside off. Shanto defends it to cover-point.
Length ball, around off, shaping in. Al Hasan hangs back and flicks it in front of square on the leg side for a single.

Short in length and slanting on the hips. Shanto is rushed as he looks to tuck it away but misses and the ball brushes his thigh pad before going into the mitts of Joshua Da Silva. An appeal for it but the umpire shakes his head. UltraEdge confirms no bat there.
Extra bounce this time, length and on middle. Shanto keeps it out.
Half-tracker, on middle. Shanto gets on top of it as he pulls it to deep mid-wicket. Three runs this time.
A full ball, this one swings back in sharply from outside off. Al Hasan looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Short of a length and on middle. Al Hasan fends it away awkwardly to square leg for a single.
A length ball, on off. Al Hasan knocks it to point for a single.
FOUR! Shanto was standing out of his crease so the keeper stands up! This is short and Shanto cuts it uppishly and over point for a boundary.
A length ball, outside off, jagging in. Shanto shoulders arms to it.
A length ball, outside off, Shanto dabs it through gully for one more.
Outside off, pushed to covers.

Four byes! This one shoots up like a rocket! Angling a length ball, around off, the ball hits the crack and climbs past Al Hasan who evades quickly and even Joshua Da Silva is taken by surprise. A boundary.
Starts off with a pacy short ball, at 141 clicks and down leg. Najmul Hossain Shanto sits under it comfortably.
Good length, on leg stump, this is tucked away towards mid-wicket.
Short again but once again down the leg side, easily left alone by Shanto.
On a good length, around off. Shanto taps it towards cover and Shakib wants a single but it's a firm call of no from Shanto.
Well bowled! Length, but gets it in that channel around off and the ball just takes off. Najmul Hossain Shanto has a slight dab at it but gets beaten for pace.
This is banged in short and over middle stump, Shanto ducks under it. Maiden!
FOUR! Up and away, intentional from Shakib. This is on the shorter side and well outside off, Shakib throws his hands at it and gets it over backward point for a boundary.
Good comeback delivery from Anderson Phillip! This is a bouncer, angled into the body and rises at a good height. Shakib Al Hasan looks to take on the hook shot but pulls out of it and rightly so.
Almost gets chopped on! Length ball, around off, Shakib looks to cut from close to the body but gets an inside edge past the stumps.
Good length, on off and there's a bit of variable bounce again. Shakib manages to keep it out.
Pitched up, outside off, this is driven through cover-point for a single.
Back of a length and over middle, Shanto hops on the back foot to keep it out.

Well, that had some serious heat behind it! Banged in short and over middle, at 143 clicks. The ball just zips through and Shakib Al Hasan does extremely well to get his head out of the line of the ball.
Another bouncer! This time again over middle but bouncing high and that allows Shakib to duck under it.
Pitches it up a bit, around middle, Shakib blocks it out.
On a good length, around middle and leg. Shakib manages to defend it out.
At the moment, it's trial via short ball for Shakib Al Hasan. Pacy bumper, over leg stump. Shakib takes his eyes off the ball as he looks to take it on and gets comprehensively beaten.
Back of a length, around off. This is dabbed down towards backward point. Maiden!
Pitches it up and angles it into off stump. Najmul Hossain Shanto solidly blocks it off the front foot.
The length is dragged back a bit this time, on middle. Shanto with another solid defensive shot.
Back of a length, this is defended off the back foot.
Banged in over middle and leg, Shanto ducks under it.

FOUR! Edged away! Length ball, outside off, Najmul Hossain Shanto plays at it with soft hands and gets an outside edge through the vacant gully region for a boundary. The 100 is up for Bangladesh and they now trail by 73 runs.
On a fuller length and around off, punched towards mid off.

Bye! Alzarri Joseph is certainly extracting a bit extra from the surface at the moment. Banged in halfway down the track and around off, the ball just takes off and goes past Shakib's outside edge. Joshua Da Silva leaps up but fumbles and the batters are able to cross over.
Back of a length, on middle. Shanto keeps it out.
Goes fuller this time, Shanto blocks it off.
Uppish but in the gap! Full again, angling into middle and leg, Najmul Hossain Shanto looks to flick but does so aerially through the vacant mid-wicket region for a brace.
Length this time, around middle and off. This is kept out by Shanto.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Najmul Hossain Shanto just couldn't resist the temptation and he will be mightily disappointed with his shot selection. This is full and wide, enticing the batter to go for the drive and Shanto goes for the expansive cover drive. Shanto's feet though go nowhere and the outside edge is found. Easy catch behind the sticks for Joshua Da Silva and Alzarri Joseph strikes after probing away for a bit. Shanto departs in the 40s and Bangladesh still trail by 70 runs.
Howout: c Joshua Da Silva b Alzarri Joseph

Commentary: West Indies are not allowing any room for comfort! A bouncer on middle. Al Hasan ducks under it.
Length and on middle, pulled to deep square leg for a single.
Length ball, outside off. Nurul punches with hard hands through covers for a single.
West Indies are serving only bouncers to Shakib! Another one outside off. Shakib tries to pull but it was too far for him.
No ball! Another short ball, outside off. Shakib leaves it and questions how many more to the umpire. A no ball signaled for height.
A length ball, around off, nips in. Shakib flicks it to square leg for a single.
Outside off, length, Nurul punches it to covers for a couple of runs.
Angling on the pads, Shakib tucks behind square on the leg side for one more.

What a ripper from Joseph! He is certainly breathing fire now! A sharp bouncer, around off, extra bounce. Nurul stands tall and is late to react to this short ball. The ball found the edge and lobs on the leg side. There is no one at short leg and it falls safely.
Bangs a bouncer on middle. Nurul sits under it. Excellent from Joshua Da Silva to get a hand to it and save a certain boundary.
On off, kept out.
Length ball, outside off. Nurul strokes it through covers for a couple of runs.
Short ball, outside off. Nurul looks to pull as he tries to ride but gets a bottom edge to the keeper. Joseph and Nurul exchange some words in the end.
A length ball, outside off. Shakib pushes to the right of covers. He wants a single but is denied by Nurul and rightly so.
Touch fuller, outside off. Shakib drives it to deep point for a single.
A length ball on middle. Nurul wrists it to square leg for a single.
Length ball, drifting outside off. Shakib waits and dabs it to the gully region. Good call from Nurul for a single as he was running on the danger side.
On a length and outside off. Nurul hits it through covers for a couple of runs.
Length ball, outside off. Nurul plays a back foot punch but straight to point.

OUT! EDGED AND GONE! Alzarri Joseph hydrates himself and gets the big wicket of Shakib Al Hasan! With that the hopes of Bangladesh getting dull as well! Another shot from a Bangladeshi batter which could have been avoided! This is on a length and outside off, it nips away off the deck. Shakib Al Hasan has a poke at it but gets an outside edge to second slip where John Campbell tries to take it but he fumbles and the ball hits him on his chest and lobs over his head kindly as he takes it on the second attempt.
Howout: c John Campbell b Alzarri Joseph

Commentary: Length and on off. Blocked out.
Five wides! This is too short and on middle. Mehidy sits and Joshua Da Silva cannot do much about it as well. It rolls behind and into the fence.
This is positive aggression from Alzarri Joseph! Short of a length and just outside off. Mehidy feels for it as he tries to push but misses.
Full and on off. Mehidy prods and defends.
Length ball, around off. Mehidy defends it solidly.
Wide! Length ball, way outside off. Mehidy leaves it alone. A wide given.
Short in length and slanting on middle. Mehidy fends it away on the leg side.
FOUR! A gentle half-volley, on middle. Nurul chips it wide of mid on and to the deep mid-wicket fence.
Angling on middle, tucked to mid-wicket for a single.
Fuller and outside off. Mehidy defends on the front foot.
Back of a length and outside off. Mehidy looks to cut but misses.
On a length and on off. Mehidy stays back on his back foot to block it.
This is outside off, it is left alone easily.
On a good length, on off. Nurul Hasan has an uncharacteristic swipe across the line but misses and gets hit on the right arm.
Back of a length, there's some width on offer. Nurul stays on the back foot and punches it sweetly through covers for three runs.
Short of a good length, on off. Mehidy blocks it off.
Banged in short and over off stump, Mehidy Hasan sways away from the line of the ball.
And again! Short and over middle, Mehidy Hasan does well to evade the line of the ball.
Joseph keeps it a bit on the shorter side and pushes it wide this time. Mehidy Hasan leaves it alone.
Starts off with a length ball, slightly wide of the off pole. Nurul Hasan punches it out solidly towards covers.
FOUR! Length again, outside off and shaping away a touch. Nurul plays it with soft hands and gets a thickish edge past gully for a boundary.
Around the top of off, Nurul puts a stride forward to defend.
On a good length this time, over off. Nurul Hasan blocks it back towards the bowler.
Roach goes very full and on off, Nurul drives it straight to the man at silly mid on.
This is banged in short and around the hips, Nurul Hasan swivel-pulls it towards deep backward square leg for one. The first over of the day produces 5 runs and Bangladesh now trail by 37 runs.
Starts off with a shortish ball, outside off. Nurul stays back and cuts it through cover-point for a run.
Back of a length, over off, this is defended off the back foot by Mehidy Hasan.
Variable bounce! Alzarri Joseph bangs it in almost halfway down the track and Mehidy attempts to shoulder arms. The ball though stays real low and bounces well in front of the keeper.
Short again, bowled with good pace and on off. Mehidy sways his head away from the line of the ball.
Good-length delivery, almost 140 clicks but just a bit too wide of the off stump. An easy leave for Mehidy Hasan on that occasion.
A well-directed short ball, lands on off and just nips away a touch. Mehidy hops back and plays inside the line of the ball.
Short of a good length, around off. Nurul presents a dead bat at it.
Length ball, angling in from outside off. Nurul backs away a bit and plays it late, through backward point for a couple of runs.
Well played! Shorter this time and angling in from around off. Nurul Hasan gets hurried on but does well to keep it down towards the gully region.
Pitched up, outside off. This is driven but straight towards covers.
Short and wide, Nurul Hasan slaps it to the right of the man at deep point for a couple of runs.
Two more! Length, outside off and slanting in. Nurul guides it away late past the slip cordon and picks up another brace.
FOUR! Mehidy Hasan is off the mark! Short, attacking the body of the batter but goes down leg, Mehidy just tickles it fine and the ball runs away into the fine leg fence.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Alzarri Joseph gets his third wicket and he's now taken three wickets in all four innings of this Test series. A well-directed short ball, close to the off pole and rising up well. Mehidy Hasan gets pushed onto the back foot and awkwardly tries to fend it away but gets the outside edge and Joshua Da Silva does the rest behind the stumps. Bangladesh 7 down now whilst trailing by 26 more runs.
Howout: c Joshua Da Silva b Alzarri Joseph

Commentary: Joseph's got an extra spring in his step now. Goes fuller and bowls it at 146 clicks, outside off. Ebadot Hossain squeezes it out on the off side.
Another short ball now, at 141 KPH and around off. The ball rises high and zips past the outside edge.
Joseph goes short again but this time gets it down leg. Ebadot Hossain looks to play at it but is beaten for pace.
Ripper of a delivery to end the over! Perfect length, at 143 clicks and angling in from around off but shapes away beautifully. Ebadot Hossain has a dab at it but gets beaten past the outside edge.
A length ball, angling down. Hasan pulls it to deep square leg but does not take a single.
SIX! He will look to cut the deficit single-handedly! Short of a length and on middle. Hasan hangs back and pulls it to deep mid-wicket for a biggie.
Short again but this is outside off. Hasan looks to cut but misses.
FOUR! Bangladesh now trail by 16 runs! A slower full ball, angling on middle. Hasan smashes it straight down the ground for a boundary.
