A single taken! Short of a length and outside off. Hasan cuts it behind square on the off side for a single. Hossain has to watchout the last ball.
He survives! On a length and around off. Hossain defends it somehow on the off side.
Sharp delivery! A bouncer on middle. Hasan fails to sit under it and takes a blow on his left shoulder.
In the air but falls safe! Short of a length and on off. Hasan looks to pull but gets a top edge and it falls safely in the square leg region. No run taken.
FOUR! Hasan is just looking to score somehow! Even if it is a hard way! Short again, well directed and Hasan rides it as he pulls it to deep square leg, in the gap for a boundary.
Short again on middle. Hasan makes room and upper cuts it to the right of third man for a couple of runs. Good fielding there.
Length ball, outside off. Hasan slaps it to deep point. This time he doesn't take a single.

FOUR! So, Ebadot Hossain will keep the strike in the next over! Short in length and on middle. Hasan makes room and clears his front leg as he flat-bats it to long on for a boundary. Bangladesh trail by just 5 runs now.
Length ball, outside off, moving away. Hossain tries to defend in the wrong line.

OUT! TAKEN! Bangladesh are 8 down now! West Indies inching closer to the win! A well-directed short ball on middle. Hossain keeps a straight bat in front of him as he tries to defend but the ball climbs and takes the shoulder of the bat. It lobs over short leg but Raymon Reifer does well to run back and dive down to his left to take a sharp catch. Bangladesh trail by 5 runs.
Howout: c Raymon Reifer b Jayden Seales

Commentary: Short of a length and around leg. Islam makes room and looks to pull but misses.

Five wides! Too short this time, following the batter on the leg side. Islam leaves it. Joshua Da Silva fails to get a hand to it and it goes behind to the fence. Bangladesh have now wiped off the deficit completely and the scores are level.

OUT! LBW! Islam goes now and Seales gets a seond wicket in the over! A slower ball, too full and angling around middle and leg. Islam fails to work it away and the ball goes under his bat and hits him on the pads. A huge shout for LBW and up goes the finger. However, Islam takes a review. Looks straight there. Ultra Edge shows no bat. Ball Tracking shows three reds and Bangladesh lose their 9th wicket.
Howout: lbw b Jayden Seales

Commentary: A fuller ball, outside off. Ahmed looks to defend but gets a thick outside edge and it falls short of the fielder near the gully region.
Length and outside off. Ahmed easily leaves it. Nurul Hasan will breathe a sigh of relief.
A short ball, slightly down the leg side. Hasan fails to pull it away.

FOUR! Bangladesh in the lead now! A very hard fought fifty for Nurul Hasan! He is fighting hard! Back of a length and around off. Hasan shuffles across and cuts it to deep point. The fielder runs to his right but fails to cut it off.
SIX! What a shot! Short again but Hasan anticipates the length and stays back to pummel it over deep mid-wicket for a biggie.
Joseph keeps the same length and Hasan works it straight down to long on. No run taken.
Short in length and on middle, pulled to deep square leg for a single. Ahmed needs to survive one ball.
Fuller and on off. Ahmed solidly defends it.
A fuller ball, outside off, nipping away. Hasan has a big swing across but misses.
No ball! Seales sees Hasan shuffle across and he bowls way outside off. Outside the pitch and a no ball is called.
On a length and wide of off. Hasan keeps it out.
Fuller and on off. Hasan lofts it over the bowler's head and to long on but again keeps the strike.
This is way outside off and on the shorter side. Hasan throws his bat at it but fails to connect.
Short ball, around odd. Hasan steps across and ducks under it. He will look to take a single now.

OUT! RUN OUT! Bangladesh are bundled out. A length ball, outside off. Hasan drops it to point. Ahmed looks for a quick single as it was the last ball but it didn't travel much away as John Campbell collects the ball at point and scores a direct-hit at the bowler's end. West Indies were confident and the replay confirms that Ahmed is well short. Not what Hasan would have hoped for but it was a tough task for him with the tail-enders on the other side. Bangladesh are all out on 186.
Howout: run out (John Campbell)

Commentary: A spicy start to the run chase! Ebadot Hossain delivers a short-pitched delivery, around off. The ball just shoots up and puts Kraigg Brathwaite in an awkward position as he tries to block. Brathwaite does well to keep it down in the end.
Pacy delivery, on a shorter length and trying to attack the pads but spilled down the leg side. Nurul Hasan does well to dive to his left and pouch it safely.
West Indies are underway! Good length, over off and jagging back in. Brathwaite hops and works it past square leg to get off the mark with a brace.
Banged in short this time and around off, Brathwaite ducks under it.
Fuller and on the pads, flicked away to fine leg for a single. Just 10 runs needed now for West Indies to win.
John Campbell is off the mark straightaway. Around the top of off, Campbell plays it late and just drops it towards backward point for a single.
Nice start from Khaled Ahmed. Fuller in length, outside off and shaping back in nicely. John Campbell shadow drives once the ball beats his bat.
Stifled appeal but nothing is given. This is drifted onto the pads, Campbell looks to flick it away but misses. The ball goes off the pads and into the keeper's mitts.
Around the top of off, solidly defended off the front foot towards cover.
Very full, around middle and leg, this is worked well in front of square on the leg side for a couple of runs.

In the air and dropped! Banged in short and on leg stump, John Campbell goes for the hook shot but mistimes it badly. The ball is skied towards the square leg fence. Ebadot Hossain runs to his right from deep backward square leg and stretches but fails to keep hold of the ball. Two taken and West Indies are just one hit away now from victory.
Back of a length, on off. Campbell pushes it out off the back foot onto the off side.
On a good length, around off. Brathwaite plays it off the back foot towards cover and picks up a quick single.
Beaten! Lovely delivery this from Ebadot Hossain, a touch fuller and in that channel around off. The ball shapes back in beautifully and beats John Campbell past the inside edge.
Good length, on middle and leg, Campbell nudges it towards square leg.
Length ball, at 140 clicks and angled across the left-hander. John Campbell lets it through to the keeper.

FOUR! Fine enough and that will be it, John Campbell has hit the winning runs! West Indies have won the Test match and the series as well. This is drifted on the pads and Campbell just tickles it 'round the corner beating the man at fine leg to his left to pick up the boundary. West Indies win by 10 wickets!
